The paper deals with the problem of planarity for graphs presented in a streaming fashion, which involves data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses planar topological drawings, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of planarity is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and graph drawing (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
